s obsessed with. And, finally, "Manganese Dioxide Dreams" offers a tantalizing insight into the author's mind as he weaves together the musings of an old man very like Tanizaki himself-Chinese and Japanese cuisine, a French murder movie, Chinese history, and the contents of a toilet bowl. These beautifully translated stories will intrigue and entertain readers who are new to Tanizaki, as well as those who have already explored the bizarre world of his imagination"--cProvided by publisher.  aDescription based on information from the publisher. 4aElectronic books.1 aChambers, Anthony H.q(Anthony Hood)1 aMcCarthy, Paul,d1944-2 aMichigan Publishing (University of Michigan)epublisher. 0aMichigan monograph series in Japanese studies ;40zAccess to the Michigan Publishing online version:uhttps://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.9409189